a Intimidation) is a skill which Monks (and a couple of other classes) have which can be used to cause fear in opponents. It is a VERY slow skill to raise, and so requires LOTS of practice - thankfully, it can be practiced while targeting anything.<br>
<br>
If you are using it in combat, you get into melee range, target your opponent, hit your Instill Doubt Hot Key, your character goes through the sequence of special attack animations, then makes a skill check. If succesful, you attempt a kick attack (using your Instill Doubt skill, not your Kick skill); if it hits, your opponent makes a saving throw vs fear - if it fails, then it runs away.<br>
<br>
Note that it fails if your special attacks aren't available, so use it when your special attacks are not greyed out (or time it so that the special attacks are available at the moment the skill check is made). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uisklant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isklant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/7/02 3:50:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1939.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Instill Doubt</span><hr size=1> Hey man, thanx for the info <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
